\f1\b\fs28 \cf2 \strokec2 3. Implementing Row-Level Security (RLS)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf2 To prevent "Tenant A" from ever seeing "Tenant B's" data (the most common SaaS security failure), you enforce isolation at the database level rather than just in your code.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 The SQL logic:
\f0\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf6 \cb7 \strokec6 SQL\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\qc\partightenfactor0

\fs48 \cf6 \
\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf9 \cb7 \strokec9 -- 1. Enable RLS on the table\cf6 \strokec6 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf10 \strokec10 ALTER\cf6 \strokec6  \cf10 \strokec10 TABLE\cf6 \strokec6  submissions ENABLE \cf10 \strokec10 ROW\cf6 \strokec6  LEVEL SECURITY;\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf9 \strokec9 -- 2. Create a policy: Only rows matching the session's tenant_id are visible\cf6 \strokec6 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf10 \strokec10 CREATE\cf6 \strokec6  POLICY tenant_isolation_policy \cf10 \strokec10 ON\cf6 \strokec6  submissions\
\cf10 \strokec10 USING\cf6 \strokec6  (tenant_id \cf2 \strokec2 =\cf6 \strokec6  current_setting(\cf11 \strokec11 'app.current_tenant_id'\cf6 \strokec6 )::uuid);\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf9 \strokec9 -- 3. In your API, before every query, set the session context:\cf6 \strokec6 \
\cf9 \strokec9 -- SET LOCAL app.current_tenant_id = 'user-tenant-uuid-here';\cf6 \strokec6 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

